      "message": "Fragile Post-Purge \"Clear Log Entry\" Delete\n\n```\n[Setup]  Run Keywords  Redfish Purge Event Log  AND  Refresh GUI\n\n# Wait until the \"clear log\" entry is visible before attempting deletion,\n# or use Redfish Purge Event Log a second time to clear the purge-generated entry.\n\nWait Until Element Is Visible  ${xpath_delete_first_row}  timeout\u003d15\nClick Element  ${xpath_delete_first_row}\nWait Until Page Contains Element  ${xpath_confirm_delete}\nClick Button  ${xpath_confirm_delete}\n# Wait for deletion to complete before proceeding.\nWait Until Element Is Not Visible  ${xpath_confirm_delete}  timeout\u003d10\n\n```\n\nAfter Redfish Purge Event Log, the BMC generates a new \"Log cleared\" event entry. The test then immediately tries to click ${xpath_delete_first_row} — but if the GUI has not refreshed yet, or if the purge-generated entry has not appeared in the GUI, the click will fail on a missing element. There is no guard (Wait Until Element Is Visible) before the click. In testing environments with slower BMC response times this is a common source of intermittent failure. Additionally, if the linked webui-vue bug (issue #142) causes \"view all\" pagination to not work, the preceding delete could compound the failure in unpredictable ways.",
