      "side": 1,
      "message": "This assertion checks that the GUI selected count equals ${create_error_logs_for_viewall} (41). However, the test setup includes a step to delete a residual \"clear log\" entry, meaning the actual post-creation log count is only 41 if exactly one purge-generated entry was deleted. If the delete failed silently, or if the BMC generated more than one entry during purge, the count will be 42+ and the assertion will fail for the wrong reason. The cleaner design is to verify GUI count \u003d\u003d Redfish count only (which is the true intent of the test).\n\n\n```\n${members}\u003d  Redfish.Get Attribute  ${EVENT_LOG_URI}Entries  Members@odata.count\n\n# Verify GUI selected count matches the Redfish API count (single authoritative assertion).\nShould Be Equal As Integers  ${selected_logs}  ${members}\n```\nor if your intent was from line number 280 ?\n```\n ${number_of_events}\u003d  Get Number Of Event Logs\n```\n\n\nThe test\u0027s documented purpose is \"verify webui entries are same as the redfish api entries.\" The redundant intermediate assertion against the hardcoded 41 introduces a brittle dependency on exact setup state. The Redfish count is the authoritative source of truth; the GUI count should match it.",
